LaSi: Lazy admin Scripted installers

# Author:  Mar2zz
# blogs: mar2zz.tweakblogs.net
# License: GNU GPL v3
# 
# please report bugs/issues @
# https://github.com/Mar2zz/LaSi/issues

The purpose of the main script LaSi.sh is to present a menu
in the terminal. This menu presents some info about accom-
panied programs and those programs can be installed from
this menu.

USAGE:
Make LaSi.sh executable with sudo chmod +x LaSi.sh
and execute with: ./LaSi.sh

When choosing a program LaSi will show some info about it
and the option to install it. If choice is 
install program X LaSi will download the latest version 
of an installer from Dropbox and starts the install. 

The installation is questiondriven. Like answer yes/no,
type location where to install etc. It's an easy way to
install programs in a terminal via ssh. 

The goal is to create a simple way to install 
programs that are not inside repo's,
but for example only on Github or googlecode.

The programs I chose are mainly written for media 
entertainment and centered around Sabnzbd and postprocessing.
They work best on headless linuxservers or dedicated linux HTPC's.

Programs supported:
* SickBeard
-- TV Shows (git)
URL: http://sickbeard.com/

* CouchPotato
-- Movies (git)
URL: http://couchpotatoapp.com/

* Periscope
-- Subtitles (svn)
http://code.google.com/p/periscope/

* AlbumIdentify
-- Music (git)
https://github.com/scottr/albumidentify

##############################################################
##############################################################

# Tested succesful on OS's:
# Ubuntu 10.4 Desktop, 
# Ubuntu 10.4 Minimal server
# XBMC Live Dharma

